<subSubSection id="2EFB5CB00B6B1BDF143D70B66A22D944" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="macau records">
<paragraph id="1E781F02B355740C8A7630A0CC105298" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Macau records.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF80F69C93448DB2ED3C9515EFBBE284" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Little Taipa, 4 Mar 2019, on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="D0868BBE775330241457EE29054FF2D3" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Oleaceae" genus="Ligustrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ligustrum sinense" order="Oleales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis id="EC6B1D01675B8D3929C35EE9E24A5439" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ligustrum sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, R Perissinotto; ibidem 13 Mar 2019, on dead tree trunk by roadside, R Perissinotto (MACT); ibidem 25 Apr 2019, on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="82FA29106D2DA7D6F837CF6FEAAB22D4" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FD5662885A612514E2FAD20ADE038D45" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. by roadside, R Perissinotto &amp; L Clennell (IZCAS).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99D9DC5C867A5740A8AFD882BA5180E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="831FB1F9D6BE6E4B5C94277824FB375E" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1E37A7675BEAF50C3E060F83E2F8A0E" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, this species has so far only been recorded from Little Taipa Hill during March-April 1999 and ranges 8-11 mm in total length and 2-3 mm in maximum width. Adults appear to be active in daytime only during the early spring and have been observed mainly feeding on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="3FEAC737844A5A6186F4F235B57103A2" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D2D021073E47F322EB82F836796E2722" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and occasionally also of 
<taxonomicName id="2C03D55B92CE8348C8C541F60FD497C7" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Oleaceae" genus="Ligustrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ligustrum sinense" order="Oleales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis id="9B5FA706076516C389C4E22B0C8D067B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ligustrum sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="ADA7FA45DB0282690F7B912ECC37ED23" author="Chou, W-I" journalOrPublisher="Owl Publishing House, Taipei" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B21" refString="Chou, W-I, 2004. The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae. Owl Publishing House, Taipei" title="The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae." year="2004">Chou (2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B4C491368CE5306AFCC9D4321B49527B" author="Chou, W-I" journalOrPublisher="Owl Publishing House, Taipei" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B22" refString="Chou, W-I, 2008. The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae (second edition). Owl Publishing House, Taipei" title="The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae (second edition)." year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
) reported that adults visit flowers and leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="D0A9D6BCBEF0079897C0BE823278AF56" authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1913" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Aceraceae" genus="Acer" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acer cinnamomifolium" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cinnamomifolium">
<emphasis id="17F9290981F7846581A36F4E1E43965F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Acer cinnamomifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Mating pairs and individuals near exit holes have also been found repeatedly on dead trunks of 
<taxonomicName id="50E239175AE7B848021EF02624C13986" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Zanthoxylum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Zanthoxylum avicennae" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="avicennae">
<emphasis id="11B7158A94092ADFB2970D855313AB37" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Zanthoxylum avicennae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, indicating that this is possibly one of the host plants for larval development (RP pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
